<|startoftext|>Dish: shrimp with a balsamic vinaigrette
Directions: in a large nonstick skillet , heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil over medium-high heat
add shrimp , and saut for 4 minutes or until just pink inside , turning once
remove shrimp from pan and keep warm
add remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil to pan , and saut shallots and garlic for another 30 seconds
return skillet to medium-high heat , and add wine and lemon juice
season with salt
cook mixture , uncovered , until sauce is reduced by 2 / 3 and has thickened , stirring often , about 15 minutes
reduce heat to medium and stir in balsamic vinegar
return to medium and cook an additional 15-20 seconds
